LOCUS       REOS4                   1196 bp ds-RNA     linear   VRL 03-AUG-1993
DEFINITION  Reovirus serotype 3, segment 4, major surface protein sigma-3 gene,
            complete coding sequence.
ACCESSION   K02739
VERSION     K02739.1
KEYWORDS    capsid protein; major outer membrane protein; membrane protein;
            outer membrane protein; sigma-3 gene.
SOURCE      Mammalian orthoreovirus 3
  ORGANISM  Mammalian orthoreovirus 3
            Viruses; dsRNA viruses; Reoviridae; Spinareovirinae; Orthoreovirus.
REFERENCE   1  (bases 1 to 1196)
  AUTHORS   Giantini,M., Seliger,L.S., Furuichi,Y. and Shatkin,A.J.
  TITLE     Reovirus type 3 genome segment S4: nucleotide sequence of the gene
            encoding a major virion surface protein
  JOURNAL   J. Virol. 52 (3), 984-987 (1984)
   PUBMED   6492267
COMMENT     Original source text: Human reovirus type 3, cDNA to viral RNA.
            The viral outer shell polypeptides, of which sigma-3 is one, impose
            structural constraints that prevent elongation of nascent
            transcripts by the virion-associated RNA-polymerase.  Sigma-3 also
            inhibits host protein synthesis in infected mouse L cells and may
            be involved in switching from cellular to viral mRNA translation at
            late times after infection.  The S4 gene also influences initiation
            of reovirus persistent infections in tissue culture cells. The plus
            (mRNA sense strand) is shown below.  It contains no obvious 'tata'
            box or 'aataa' poly-A signal, but it does have the 3' terminal
            pentanucleotide common to reovirus plus strands.
